WEBVTT

00:02.302 --> 00:02.534
               .

00:02.536 --> 00:07.406
   - YOU GOTTA DO SOMETHING.
- MADISON, YOU ARE GOING TO BED.

00:07.408 --> 00:09.675
      - HONEY, I NEED YOU
       TO TAKE THE BABY.

00:09.677 --> 00:11.176
             - NO!
- MADISON, YOU ARE GOING TO BED.

00:11.178 --> 00:12.177
         - OH, MY GOD.

00:12.179 --> 00:14.179
   - WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

00:14.181 --> 00:15.414
     WE'RE SUPPOSED TO MEET
AT THE BOWLING ALLEY IN AN HOUR.

00:15.416 --> 00:16.415
         I'M NOT READY.
        - YEAH, WE WERE,

00:16.417 --> 00:19.284
   A REALLY ANNOYING TENDENCY
      TO BAIL LAST MINUTE

00:19.286 --> 00:20.386
       ON BOYS' NIGHT...

00:20.388 --> 00:22.287
             - NO!
 - THE OTHER ONE OF US DECIDED

00:22.289 --> 00:23.489
        TO PICK YOU UP,
    NEGATING THE POSSIBILITY

00:23.491 --> 00:24.623
          OF THE BAIL.

00:24.625 --> 00:27.626
 CAN YOU MAKE THAT STOP CRYING?
         - NO BEDTIME!

00:27.628 --> 00:29.194
          - I'M SORRY.
         - NO, NO, NO!

00:29.196 --> 00:30.195
     - YOU GOTTA GO TO BED.

00:30.197 --> 00:31.430
   - I DON'T WANNA GO TO BED!

00:31.432 --> 00:32.564
      - YEAH, I DON'T WANT
      TO GO TO BED EITHER,

00:32.566 --> 00:34.366
      BUT YOU DON'T SEE ME
        RAGING ABOUT IT.

00:34.368 --> 00:36.668
             - NO!
   - GET A GRIP, TINY PERSON.

00:36.670 --> 00:38.303
   - PUT YOUR JAMMY PANTS ON
           RIGHT NOW,

00:38.305 --> 00:41.140
   - HEY, IF NO CUDDLY-WUDDLY
         WITH YOUR MOM

00:41.142 --> 00:43.208
   IS AN OPTION, I WOULD JUMP
 ON THAT RIGHT NOW, BABY GIRL.

00:43.210 --> 00:45.077
     - WELL, LOOK WHO LEFT
          THE BIG CITY

00:45.079 --> 00:46.278
  TO SLUM IT IN THE EAST BAY.

00:46.280 --> 00:50.716
  - AAH, CAN'T WE DO SOMETHING
     TO STOP THIS, PLEASE?

00:50.718 --> 00:52.317
         GOD! SO NOISY.

00:52.319 --> 00:54.686
        THAT MUTES THEM
   AND FREEZES THEM IN PLACE,

00:54.688 --> 00:58.357
- ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO, LET'S GO.
   - HEY, SINCE YOU'RE HERE,

00:58.359 --> 01:00.292
   THERE'S ACTUALLY SOMETHING
WE WANTED TO TALK TO YOU ABOUT.

01:00.294 --> 01:02.361
           - [sighs]
             - NOW.

01:02.363 --> 01:06.365
           ALL RIGHT,
      IN THE EVENT THAT...

01:06.367 --> 01:08.067
           [whispers]
        SOMETHING TRAGIC

01:08.069 --> 01:10.302
         SHOULD HAPPEN
        TO LAURIE AND I,

01:10.304 --> 01:11.537
       WE WOULD LIKE YOU

01:11.539 --> 01:13.272
    TO BE JONAH'S GODFATHER.

01:13.274 --> 01:15.174
        - WELL, NOT WE.
              HE.

01:15.176 --> 01:16.508
          I JUST WANT
      TO MAKE THAT CLEAR.

01:16.510 --> 01:18.110
             - WE.
            - WHAT?

01:18.112 --> 01:20.312
      WAIT, IF SOMETHING--
        SOMETHING TRA--

01:20.314 --> 01:24.249
       TRAGIC HAPPENS...

01:24.251 --> 01:25.451
    YOU WANT ME TO RAISE IT?

01:25.453 --> 01:27.252
   - I MEAN, WE'D HAVE TO DIE
        SIMULTANEOUSLY,

01:27.254 --> 01:29.388
        AND THE CHANCES
    OF THAT HAPPENING ARE--

01:29.390 --> 01:30.622
       - I'M NEVER DYING.

01:30.624 --> 01:32.191
           - [crying]

01:32.193 --> 01:34.393
        - SO--WOW, GUYS.

01:34.395 --> 01:35.761
        THAT IS SO, UH--

01:35.763 --> 01:38.130
       I MEAN, HE'S CUTE.
     HE'S VERY, VERY CUTE.

01:38.132 --> 01:39.798
     BUT I'M JUST GONNA GO
          WITH A "NO."

01:39.800 --> 01:41.567
           YOU KNOW.
            - WHAT?

01:41.569 --> 01:44.236
     - WE'RE GOING BOWLING!
    LET'S GO. FIVE MINUTES.

01:44.238 --> 01:46.105
      I'M GIVING YOU FIVE
   'CAUSE I'M A GOOD FRIEND.

01:46.107 --> 01:49.108
       [Brick + Mortar's
            <i> Old Boy]</i>

01:49.110 --> 01:52.211
              ¶ ¶

01:52.213 --> 01:54.379
     - ¶ WHAT UP, WHAT UP,
           OLD BOY? ¶

01:54.381 --> 01:55.514
   - ALL RIGHT, YOU'RE BEING
         WEIRDLY QUIET.

01:55.516 --> 01:58.383
         - MY CHILD HAS
      NO GODPARENT, WILL.

01:58.385 --> 01:59.818
           - [scoffs]
   LET'S JUST MOVE ON, OKAY?

01:59.820 --> 02:01.353
  WE'RE GOING BOWLING TONIGHT.

02:01.355 --> 02:03.288
       [cell phone rings]
WHO IS THAT? DON'T PICK THAT UP.

02:03.290 --> 02:05.624
   - CHUCK IT OUT THE WINDOW.
           CHUCK IT--

02:05.626 --> 02:06.792
         - HEY, HONEY.

02:06.794 --> 02:08.594
          OH, MY GOD,
    YOU'VE GOTTA BE KIDDING.

02:08.596 --> 02:10.294
           ALL RIGHT.
           - OH, NO.

02:10.297 --> 02:11.530
       - I GOTTA GO HOME.
            - WHAT?

02:11.532 --> 02:14.166
 - WE'RE TRANSITIONING MADISON
        ONTO THE POTTY,

02:14.168 --> 02:15.767
       AND SHE WON'T POOP
       UNLESS I'M THERE.

02:15.769 --> 02:18.170
    I'M HER POTTY MOTIVATOR.
  IT'S ACTUALLY KIND OF SWEET.

02:18.172 --> 02:21.206
          - [stammers]
         IT'S HORRIFIC.

02:21.208 --> 02:22.774
      YOU ARE NOT BAILING
         ON ME TONIGHT.

02:22.776 --> 02:24.343
     - IT'S ONLY GONNA TAKE
   ABOUT AN HOUR, ALL RIGHT?

02:24.345 --> 02:25.477
       - AN HOUR TO POOP?
   - I'LL BE RIGHT BACK OUT.

02:25.479 --> 02:26.478
       JUST TAKE ME HOME.

02:26.480 --> 02:28.514
          TILL WE GET
     TO THE BOWLING ALLEY.

02:28.516 --> 02:29.815
       - DUDE, SERIOUSLY.
             - NO.

02:29.817 --> 02:32.284
   I AM NOT LETTING YOU BAIL
         ON ME TONIGHT.

02:32.286 --> 02:34.786
        - YOU KNOW WHAT?

02:34.788 --> 02:36.421
        - ANDY, DO NOT--

02:36.423 --> 02:38.824
        [tires screech]

02:38.826 --> 02:40.626
     ANDY, COME BACK HERE!

02:40.628 --> 02:42.427
      WE'RE BOWLING, ANDY!

02:42.429 --> 02:44.530
      - ¶ TRACK YOU DOWN ¶

02:44.532 --> 02:46.365
         ¶ BY THE RIVER
     WITH THEM COLD BOYS ¶

02:46.367 --> 02:48.500
       ¶ IT TOOK A WHILE
         TO FIND YOU ¶

02:48.502 --> 02:50.335
      - TJ, WHAT UP, DUDE?

02:50.337 --> 02:51.837
        CROSBY, WHAT UP?

02:51.839 --> 02:53.172
       BILLY, GREAT NEWS.

02:53.174 --> 02:54.473
       I GOT A BIG NIGHT
           LINED UP.

02:54.475 --> 02:55.741
      IT COULD GET CRAZY,

02:55.743 --> 02:58.243
     DUDE, THIS IS GONNA BE
THE BIGGEST NIGHT OF YOUR LIFE!

02:58.245 --> 02:59.378
       [imitates ringing]

02:59.380 --> 03:00.445
    YOU'RE THE FIRST PERSON
          I'M CALLING.

03:00.447 --> 03:02.314
     NUMBER ONE ON MY LIST,
          EVERY TIME.

03:02.316 --> 03:04.349
            SAY YES.
       SAY YES, SAY YES.

03:04.351 --> 03:06.385
            SAY YES.
       OH, KID'S RECITAL?

03:06.387 --> 03:08.287
 WAIT, WHEN DID YOU HAVE A KID?
        YOU'RE MARRIED?

03:08.289 --> 03:10.355
 YEAH, YOU'RE THE FIRST PERSON
       I'M CALLING, MAN.

03:10.357 --> 03:11.857
             WHAT?
    YOU MOVED TO CINCINNATI?

03:11.859 --> 03:13.192
         REALLY, DUDE?

03:13.194 --> 03:14.293
            [groans]

03:14.295 --> 03:15.894
   - OH, TROUBLE IN PARADISE.

03:15.896 --> 03:18.297
      - NO, IT'S JUST ANDY
  BAILED ON ME AGAIN TONIGHT,

03:18.299 --> 03:19.565
     AND I ALREADY PREPAID
         FOR THE LANES,

03:19.567 --> 03:21.600
         SO IT'S LIKE--

03:21.602 --> 03:22.668
              HEY.

03:22.670 --> 03:24.236
   IS THERE ANY CHANCE THAT--

03:24.238 --> 03:25.704
     - OH, LET ME STOP YOU
          RIGHT THERE

03:25.706 --> 03:27.706
      BEFORE YOU EMBARRASS
          BOTH OF US.

03:27.708 --> 03:30.275
  I'M NOT GOING TO GO BOWLING
        WITH YOU, WILL.

03:30.277 --> 03:32.244
           I'M SORRY.

03:32.246 --> 03:36.281
      - YEAH, I WAS GOING
     TO ASK MARCUS, FIONA.

03:36.283 --> 03:37.316
             - OH.

03:37.318 --> 03:38.317
          - YES! YES!

03:38.319 --> 03:39.885
     I TOTALLY BOWL, WILL!

03:39.887 --> 03:41.520
  AND I'M SO MUCH MORE AWESOME
           THAN ANDY!

03:41.522 --> 03:43.555
       - [snaps fingers]
  CAR'S LEAVING IN 30 SECONDS.

03:43.557 --> 03:45.591
      IF YOU'RE NOT IN IT,
        I'M OUTTA HERE.

03:45.593 --> 03:47.259
    [hip-hop music playing]

03:47.261 --> 03:48.594
    FIRST ANDY BAILS ON ME,

03:48.596 --> 03:49.595
   AND NOW HE'S NOT ANSWERING
           MY TEXTS.

03:49.597 --> 03:51.597
       WHAT'S THAT ABOUT?
             - OH.

03:51.599 --> 03:52.798
  THANKS FOR BRINGING ME HERE.

03:52.800 --> 03:55.234
      OOH, YOU SHOULD FEEL
           MY PULSE.

03:55.236 --> 03:57.002
    THIS IS THE MOST EXCITED
        I'VE EVER BEEN.

03:57.004 --> 04:00.439
  - YEAH? IS IT MORE EXCITING
      THAN A POOPING BABY?

04:03.443 --> 04:05.344
             - YES.

04:05.346 --> 04:06.945
       [girls squealing]

04:06.947 --> 04:08.647
       - ALL RIGHT, DUDE.
         LET'S SEE IT.

04:08.649 --> 04:11.650
       [Psychic Friend's
        <i> The Kids Are OK]</i>

04:11.652 --> 04:13.285
  - ¶ JOHNNY ALWAYS THOUGHT ¶

04:13.287 --> 04:15.387
    ¶ THAT HE HAD IT MADE ¶

04:15.389 --> 04:16.387
           - [sighs]

04:16.390 --> 04:18.923
         JUST STRAIGHT
        DOWN THE MIDDLE.

04:18.926 --> 04:21.692
   - ¶ N.Y., S.F., OR L.A. ¶

04:21.695 --> 04:23.695
           - [groans]
             OKAY.

04:23.697 --> 04:24.830
    THIRD TIME'S THE CHARM.

04:24.832 --> 04:27.299
      - ALL RIGHT, BUDDY.
             DO IT.

04:27.301 --> 04:30.335
  - ¶ REALLY CAN'T COMPLAIN ¶

04:30.337 --> 04:31.670
      ¶ EVERYTHING WRONG ¶

04:31.672 --> 04:33.272
      - GOT A GOOD FEELING
     ABOUT THIS ONE, WILL.

04:33.274 --> 04:34.273
        - YEAH, ME TOO.

04:34.275 --> 04:38.377
    - ¶ THE KIDS ARE OKAY ¶

04:40.346 --> 04:42.581
  - HEY, WILL, DO YOU THINK WE
     COULD USE THE BUMPERS?

04:42.583 --> 04:45.284
  I'VE REALLY GOT MY HEART SET
     ON REACHING THE PINS.

04:45.286 --> 04:46.985
    MAYBE EVEN TOPPLING ONE.

04:46.987 --> 04:49.388
          - ANDY AND I
   DON'T USE BUMPERS, MARCUS.

04:49.390 --> 04:52.357
    AND THAT IS NOT INTENDED
           AS A JOKE.

04:52.359 --> 04:56.428
   - I DIDN'T SEE IT AS ONE.

04:56.430 --> 04:59.364
        OH, OH, OH, OH.

04:59.366 --> 05:00.832
        - ANDY WOULD'VE.

05:00.834 --> 05:04.436
    - ¶ MONEY, MONEY, MONEY
        MAKE US SMILE ¶

05:04.438 --> 05:05.904
         - HERE WE GO.

05:05.906 --> 05:09.408
  [Brett Dennen's <i> Comeback Kid</i>
        <i> (That's My Dog)]</i>

05:09.410 --> 05:11.743
         ¶ WELL, MAYBE
    IT'S THE COMMON CURSE ¶

05:11.745 --> 05:15.347
     ¶ MAYBE THINGS GET BAD
    BEFORE THEY GET WORSE ¶

05:15.349 --> 05:17.015
         ¶ I DON'T WANT
      TO BECOME SOMEONE ¶

05:17.017 --> 05:20.752
      ¶ WHO CAN'T LIVE UP
TO WHAT I ALREADY DONE, DON'T ¶

05:20.754 --> 05:22.321
   ¶ HERE COMES A COMEBACK ¶

05:22.323 --> 05:25.023
       ¶ THE KID IS BACK,
       IS BACK ON TRACK ¶

05:25.025 --> 05:28.026
   ¶ AND THERE GOES MY HERO ¶

05:28.028 --> 05:31.897
      ¶ HE'S THE UNDERDOG,
 HE'S COMING OUT ON TOP, AND ¶

05:31.899 --> 05:34.366
     [cheers and applause]

05:35.935 --> 05:36.368
               .

05:36.370 --> 05:38.070
            - WILL.
       SHE POOPED, WILL.

05:38.072 --> 05:41.773
    WILL! WE CAN GO OUT NOW!

05:41.775 --> 05:42.774
             WILL?

05:42.776 --> 05:43.975
      - HE'S--HE'S NOT IN.

05:43.977 --> 05:44.976
           - OH, HEY.

05:44.978 --> 05:46.645
        - HE'S NOT HERE.

05:46.647 --> 05:48.347
          - I'M ANDY,
      WILL'S BEST FRIEND.

05:48.349 --> 05:49.715
         YOU'RE FIONA.
   WE MET BRIEFLY, REMEMBER?

05:49.717 --> 05:51.550
         - YES! HELLO.
       - HOW'S IT GOING?

05:51.552 --> 05:53.785
   - HE TOOK MY SON, MARCUS,
            BOWLING.

05:53.787 --> 05:55.687
           - [sighs]
      THAT'S UNBELIEVABLE.

05:55.689 --> 05:56.855
            I'M S--
          [stammering]

05:56.857 --> 05:58.423
  I HAVE A HALL PASS TONIGHT,

05:58.425 --> 06:00.025
    AND HE WAS JUST SUPPOSED
     TO WAIT FOR ONE HOUR,

06:00.027 --> 06:01.526
        SO I COULD HELP
       MY DAUGHTER POOP.

06:01.528 --> 06:04.396
   SHE WON'T POOP WITHOUT ME
       HOLDING HER HAND.

06:04.398 --> 06:06.698
  - YOU KNOW, MY SON, MARCUS,
       WAS A LATE POOPER.

06:06.700 --> 06:08.800
    AND IT WAS ROUGH GOING.

06:08.802 --> 06:11.002
    BUT ACTUALLY, IT TURNED
        OUT TO BE RATHER

06:11.004 --> 06:13.672
  A BONDING EXPERIENCE FOR US.
             - OH.

06:13.674 --> 06:14.673
WHAT KIND OF WINE YOU GOT THERE?

06:14.675 --> 06:16.508
       - GLASS OF SHIRAZ.
             - OH.

06:16.510 --> 06:17.709
       - SHIRAZ-A-MATAZ.

06:17.711 --> 06:20.846
     - AH, SHIRAZ-A-MATAZ.
          - [laughing]

06:20.848 --> 06:23.849
      - I'VE NEVER HAD IT.
             - MM.

06:23.851 --> 06:26.752
     - PROBABLY DELICIOUS.
    - NOT REALLY, ACTUALLY.

06:26.754 --> 06:27.986
    DOES THE TRICK, THOUGH.

06:27.988 --> 06:31.056
             - AH.
          - [laughing]

06:35.061 --> 06:36.395
         [bright music]

06:36.397 --> 06:38.029
     - OH, HERE'S THE ONE.
           - [gasps]

06:38.031 --> 06:39.831
          SO GORGEOUS,
          AREN'T THEY?

06:39.833 --> 06:40.732
    - AND WILL DOESN'T EVEN
           KNOW THEM.

06:40.734 --> 06:41.967
            I MEAN,
       WOULD IT KILL HIM

06:41.969 --> 06:43.135
     TO LEARN THEIR NAMES?

06:43.137 --> 06:44.836
  - HE MUST KNOW THEIR NAMES.
             - NO.

06:44.838 --> 06:46.972
HE ONLY KNOWS THAT MY KID'S NAME
            IS JONAH

06:46.974 --> 06:48.573
   BECAUSE HE STOLE THE NAME

06:48.575 --> 06:49.741
    WHEN HE WAS USING MARCUS
          TO GET LAID.

06:49.743 --> 06:52.644
     - YES, I RECALL THAT.
       WHAT DO YOU THINK?

06:52.646 --> 06:54.413
     - I REALLY LIKE THAT,
       BUT I'M A TOE GUY.

06:54.415 --> 06:55.680
     - IT'S GOOD, ISN'T IT?

06:55.682 --> 06:56.848
   TOES DON'T NEED TO SCREAM
       ANYTHING, DO THEY?

06:56.850 --> 06:58.116
            - WELL--
      - RIGHT, MORE BOOZE.

06:58.118 --> 06:59.818
           [clatter]
          OH, BUGGER.

06:59.820 --> 07:01.686
        DO YOU SEE THAT?
     I'VE GOT TO FIX THAT.

07:01.688 --> 07:02.754
           - LET ME.
          I CAN DO IT.

07:02.756 --> 07:04.656
        - ARE YOU HANDY?
         - SO HANDY...

07:04.658 --> 07:06.491
       THAT THEY CALL ME
         "HANDY ANDY."

07:06.493 --> 07:07.793
         - THEY DON'T.

07:07.795 --> 07:10.662
    - BUT YOU GOT ANY TOOLS?
     I CAN PROBABLY FIX IT.

07:10.664 --> 07:13.598
   - YEAH, I'VE GOT A LOVELY
  CROCHET TOOL BELT, ACTUALLY.

07:13.600 --> 07:14.933
      - OKAY, YOU'RE GONNA
           LOVE THIS.

07:14.935 --> 07:16.735
     ALL RIGHT, WE'LL TAKE
       THE USUAL, KITTY--

07:16.737 --> 07:18.804
         TWO PRIME RIB
       FRENCH DIP SLIDERS

07:18.806 --> 07:21.039
     AND TWO BELGIAN FRIES
   WITH THE PEPPER JACK MAYO.

07:21.041 --> 07:23.475
 - OH, UH, NO PEPPER JACK MAYO
            FOR ME.

07:23.477 --> 07:26.578
        THEY ARE FAMOUS
  FOR THEIR PEPPER JACK MAYO.

07:26.580 --> 07:30.148
  - WELL, I'M FAMOUS FOR BEING
      LACTOSE INTOLERANT.

07:30.150 --> 07:33.051
  DO YOU HAVE ANY HEMP SPREAD?

07:35.221 --> 07:36.822
   THE LOOK ON YOUR FACE SAYS
         YOU COULD USE

07:36.824 --> 07:38.790
   SOME HEMP SPREAD TOO, BRO.

07:38.792 --> 07:40.992
      - YOU KNOW HOW HARD
       I WORKED ON LAURIE

07:40.994 --> 07:43.795
TO GET HER TO AGREE TO HAVE WILL
       BE THE GODFATHER?

07:43.797 --> 07:45.096
  RIGHT? I LOVE HER TO DEATH,

07:45.098 --> 07:46.965
  BUT SHE'S JUST NOT AS CHILL
       AS YOU ARE, FIONA.

07:46.967 --> 07:49.034
      - OH, THANKS, ANDY.

07:49.036 --> 07:51.970
   YOU KNOW, AND THEN HE JUST
      FLAT-OUT REJECTS ME.

07:51.972 --> 07:53.839
      I MEAN, DOESN'T EVEN
       TAKE IT SERIOUSLY.

07:53.841 --> 07:54.806
      HE'S SUPPOSED TO BE
        MY BEST FRIEND,

07:54.808 --> 07:56.608
     AND HE DOESN'T EVEN--
             - YO!

07:56.610 --> 07:57.742
      JUST DROPPING OFF--

07:57.744 --> 07:58.944
         WHAT THE HELL
       IS GOING ON HERE?

07:58.946 --> 07:59.945
       - HELLO, DARLING.

07:59.947 --> 08:01.947
        - DID YOU PAINT
         YOUR TOENAILS?

08:01.949 --> 08:03.582
     - JUST TESTING COLORS.

08:03.584 --> 08:04.816
      NOTHING'S GOING ON.

08:04.818 --> 08:06.551
     HANDY ANDY IS ENJOYING
          THE COMPANY

08:06.553 --> 08:07.786
    OF A CONSIDERATE FRIEND.

08:07.788 --> 08:09.221
 - NICE BAILING TONIGHT, WUSS.

08:09.223 --> 08:12.657
        - OH, I'M SORRY.
   WHAT'D YOU SAY, NOT JONAH?

08:12.659 --> 08:13.658
            [laughs]
              OH!

08:13.660 --> 08:14.759
    - YEAH, NO, HE'S MY KID.

08:14.761 --> 08:15.861
            - RIGHT.

08:15.863 --> 08:19.664
         ONE LOUSY HOUR
    OF INCONVENIENCE TO YOU,

08:19.666 --> 08:20.732
    AND THEN WE COULD'VE HAD
         OUR NIGHT OUT.

08:20.734 --> 08:22.834
            BUT NO.
   - I AGREE WITH HANDY ANDY.

08:22.836 --> 08:24.703
     - WELL, I WAS ENJOYING
    THE COMPANY OF A FRIEND

08:24.705 --> 08:27.205
    WHO'S FREE TO HAVE FUN,
          WINE TEETH.

08:27.207 --> 08:29.508
      PROVIDED HE FINISHES
      HIS HOMEWORK FIRST.

08:29.510 --> 08:31.109
   - WELL, I THINK HANDY ANDY
      NEEDS TO GROW A SET

08:31.111 --> 08:32.210
       AND QUIT BAILING.

08:32.212 --> 08:33.879
           - MARCUS!
        - IN MY DEFENSE,

08:33.881 --> 08:35.714
         I HAVE NO IDEA
    WHAT ANY OF THAT MEANS.

08:35.716 --> 08:37.649
        - YOU KNOW WHAT?
        I'M OUTTA HERE.

08:37.650 --> 08:38.817
     THANKS FOR A FUN TIME.

08:38.818 --> 08:41.219
          - OH, I SEE.
         BAILING AGAIN.

08:41.221 --> 08:44.155
       - I'M NOT BAILING.
   I'M JUST BLOWING YOU OFF.

08:44.157 --> 08:48.159
       [whistles, laughs]

08:48.161 --> 08:49.828
    [door opens and closes]
          - [inhales]

08:49.830 --> 08:51.062
    IT WAS A SHIRAZ, RIGHT?

08:51.064 --> 08:52.964
            - 2005.

08:52.966 --> 08:55.800
 - ANDY IS EITHER NEVER AROUND,
          WHICH SUCKS,

08:55.802 --> 08:58.570
    OR HE BAILS COMPLETELY,
          WHICH BLOWS.

08:58.572 --> 09:02.107
        SO AS A FRIEND,
     ANDY SUCKS AND BLOWS.

09:02.109 --> 09:04.776
      - YES, I CAN SEE HOW
     HIS DEMANDING SCHEDULE

09:04.778 --> 09:07.746
