15:22.155 --> 15:23.488
        IF THAT'S COOL.

15:23.490 --> 15:24.923
           - MM-HMM.

15:24.925 --> 15:26.658
    SO YOU GUYS ARE GONNA--
      WHILE I'M DOWN HERE.

15:26.660 --> 15:28.159
      I MEAN, THAT'S COOL.

15:28.161 --> 15:29.661
      I MEAN, NOT REALLY,
   BUT LET'S JUST GO WITH IT.

15:29.663 --> 15:32.430
       - HEY, THANK YOU.
      - OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.

15:32.432 --> 15:35.199
    OKAY. I'VE GOT A BOTTLE
      PREPARED FOR JONAH,

15:35.201 --> 15:37.468
   BUT IF HE'S STILL HUNGRY,
  THERE'S CUBES OF FROZEN PEAS

15:37.470 --> 15:38.569
   AND SQUASH IN THE FREEZER.

15:38.571 --> 15:40.471
         MICROWAVE THEM
        FOR 32 SECONDS.

15:40.473 --> 15:42.340
        NOT 35, NOT 30.

15:42.342 --> 15:44.242
   YOU CAN CUT UP SOME APPLE
           FOR THEM,

15:44.244 --> 15:47.278
   IT'S FULL OF ANTIOXIDANTS.
        - OKAY, COME ON.

15:47.280 --> 15:48.279
     - MAKE SURE YOU CUT IT
       INTO SMALL SLICES,

15:48.281 --> 15:49.647
    SO THEY DON'T--[chokes]
             OKAY.

15:49.649 --> 15:51.416
       YOU CAN PUT JONAH
          IN HIS CRIB,

15:51.418 --> 15:53.251
          BUT YOU MUST
       SWADDLE HIM FIRST.

15:53.253 --> 15:55.119
           YOU MUST.
             ALSO--

15:55.121 --> 15:56.454
      - ENOUGH. HONESTLY,
  YOU SOUND LIKE YOU'RE GOING

